    <h1>Private Limited Company Incorporation</h1>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>📝 Overview</h2>
        <p>A Private Limited Company (Pvt Ltd) is the gold standard for businesses in India. It treats the business as an independent "legal person" separate from its owners.</p>
        <p><strong>Power of Limited Liability:</strong> Your personal bank accounts, homes, and assets are protected by law.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>👥 Eligibility</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Minimum 2 Directors (One must be an Indian resident).</li>
            <li>Minimum 2 Shareholders.</li>
            <li>Physical office address in India.</li>
            <li>No minimum capital requirement.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>📁 Documents Required</h2>
        <p><strong>For Directors/Shareholders:</strong> PAN Card, [Aadhaar Redacted], Identity Proof (Passport/Voter ID), Recent Bank Statement/Utility Bill (last 2 months), Passport-sized photograph.</p>
        <p><strong>For Registered Office:</strong> Electricity bill and NOC from property owner (or Rent Agreement).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>⚡ The Process</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Digital Signatures (DSC):</strong> Obtaining secure electronic signatures for all directors.</li>
            <li><strong>Name Reservation:</strong> Reserving a unique name via MCA.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Drafting:</strong> Drafting MOA and AOA.</li>
            <li><strong>Submission:</strong> Final SPICe+ portal submission.</li>
            <li><strong>Certificate & Kits:</strong> Receiving COI, PAN, and TAN.</li>
        </ol>
